	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require a tiny bead of amber, crystal, or glass.</p><p></p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>When cast, a glowing bead appears at a point within range. The bead explodes when your concentration ends, or when you choose to end the spell.</p></li><li><p>Base damage is [[/damage 12d6 fire]] damage.* At the end of each of your turns, if the bead has not yet detonated, the damage increases by [[/damage 1d6 fire]]{1d6}.</p></li><li><p>If the bead is touched before detonation, the creature must make a <strong>[[/save DEX]]{Dexterity Save}</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> The bead immediately detonates.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> The creature may throw the bead up to 40 ft. When it strikes a creature or solid object, it explodes.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>[[/save DEX]]{Dexterity Save}</strong></p><p>The fire spreads around corners, igniting flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried, which take [[/damage 1d10 fire]] damage every round until extinguished as an action.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes the accumulated fire damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 fire]]{1d6} for each spell level above 7th.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-MJyHct0hk2xcEz89\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>The limited uses value of this spell tracks the number of rounds that have passed since the initial casting and starts at 0.</p><p>The <strong>Turn End Damage Increase</strong> activity will increase that value by 1.</p><p>The <strong>Trigger Explosion</strong> activity calculates the total damage based on the limited uses.</p><p>If you would prefer manual tracking, you can use <strong>Trigger Explosion's</strong> Situational Bonus dialog to add the extra d6s and ignore the <strong>Turn End Damage</strong> Increase activity.</p></section>",
			"chat": ""
		},
